Binius64 — GF(2^128) Field Arithmetic — License & Provenance
============================================================

SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT

Copyright (c) 2025-2026 The Soqucoin Core developers

Original work by Soqucoin: a clean-room implementation of GF(2^128) binary-field
arithmetic for the Binius / Sangria proof system. Licensed under the MIT License;
the full license text is in the repository root `COPYING`.

This module implements standard binary-field arithmetic. The field polynomial is
the NIST SP 800-38D pentanomial (the same GHASH polynomial used by AES-GCM); such
references describe the mathematics and are not third-party source attributions.
Portions were rewritten as part of the Halborn Extension Audit remediation
(findings SOQ-A001..A004; see the SECURITY NOTE headers in the source).
